Input.Category: Ask a question about the structure of the document.
Input.Description: A good question references parts of the document by name, number, or page, and asks about content in those parts.
Input.Positive_Example_1: What is the main takeaway from section 5?
Input.Positive_Example_2: What counterexamples are provided in paragraph 3, section #1?
Input.Negative_Example_1: How many sections are there in the document? (too easy to answer)
Input.Negative_Example_2: What is the title of the document? (too easy to answer)
Answer.question: Can you tell me more about what the section on the right hand side is about?

Title: Come up with a question for a document
Description: Given a question, brainstorm a question to ask
Input.Category: Ask a question about the document.
Input.Description: A good question can be fully answered by the information in the document and is not self-evident (not able to be verified with a quick scan).
Input.Positive_Example_1: Is 2pm on Wednesday free?
Input.Positive_Example_2: What evidence is used to support the author's conclusion in section #8?
Input.Negative_Example_1: What is the title of subsection #4? (too easy to answer)
Answer.question: Who is the top person in charge of the 4-H program in Butler County?

Title: Come up with a question for a document

Answer.question: Which graph in Figure 2 shows the most positive trend?

Input.Positive_Example_2: Can you simplify this: "In mice, immunoregulatory APCs express the dendritic  cell (DC) marker CD11c, and one or more distinctive  markers (CD8, B220, DX5)."
Input.Negative_Example_1: Remove all typos. (too broad, does not refer to specific text)
Answer.question: Can you rewrite the abstract in an easy-to-understand format? Here is the abstract: Common variable immunodeficiency (CVID) is an heterogeneous syndrome characterized by decreased levels of serum Ig and recurrent bacterial infection. Here, we were interested to study whether a qualitative defect of the affinity Ab maturation process could be combined to the low level of serum Ig in a cohort of 38 CVID patients. For this, we designed a novel and rapid screening test for the detection of hypomutated V gene expressed by memory B cells. This test delineated a subset of 9/38 (23%) CVID patients with an abnormal pattern of Ig V gene mutation. The mean frequency of V gene mutation of this subset was significantly lower (1.74%) compared with other CVID patients (5.46%) and normal donors (6.5%) (p < 0.0001). The mean age of this subgroup was significantly higher than other hypogammaglobulinemic patients with normal levels of V gene mutation (p < 0.02), whereas no difference in the duration of symptoms was noted between the two groups. This suggests that hypomutation characterizes patients who began CVID late in life. Recently, it was shown that non-Ig sequences, such as the intronic BCL-6 gene, could be the target of the somatic hypermutation process in normal memory B cells. Our finding of a normal mutation frequency of the BCL-6 gene in two hypomutated CVID point to a defect of the Ig targeting of hypermutation machinery in these cases. The Journal of Immunology, 2000, 165: 4725–4730.

Input.Category: Ask for specific content to be extracted from the document.
Input.Description: A good extraction task asks to find content that's answerable with one or more highlights in the document.
Input.Positive_Example_1: Find all the councilmembers mentioned in this document.
Input.Positive_Example_2: What are the three central claims of the author?
Input.Negative_Example_1: "How many times does the author mention the title character?" (not relevant question)
Input.Negative_Example_2: Write a short summary. (does not specify summary content)
Answer.question: How many garlic cloves should be included in the Broccoli Raab and Carmelized onions dish and how?

Title: Come up with a question for a document
Description: Given a question, brainstorm a question to ask
Input.Category: Ask for a rewrite of some text in the document.
Input.Description:
Copy some text from the document and ask for it to be rewritten in a certain way,or with a certain style.
 
A good task contains the text to be rewritten, and a description of how it should be rewritten.
Input.Positive_Example_1: Can you rewrite this in more modern language: "The thousand injuries of Fortunato I had borne as best I could. But when he ventured upon insult, I vowed revenge."
Input.Positive_Example_2: Can you simplify this: "In mice, immunoregulatory APCs express the dendritic  cell (DC) marker CD11c, and one or more distinctive  markers (CD8, B220, DX5)."
Input.Negative_Example_1: Remove all typos. (too broad, does not refer to specific text)
Answer.question: Can you rewrite the part that says, "The Agency had concerns about the technique used to cross the watercourse east of the pump station."

Title: Come up with a question for a document
Description: Given a question, brainstorm a question to ask
Input.Category: Ask a question about the document.
Input.Description: A good question can be fully answered by the information in the document and is not self-evident (not able to be verified with a quick scan).
Input.Positive_Example_1: Is 2pm on Wednesday free?
Input.Positive_Example_2: What evidence is used to support the author's conclusion in section #8?
Input.Negative_Example_1: What is the title of subsection #4? (too easy to answer)
Answer.question: Are the churches all located in the same town?

Title: Come up with a question for a document
Description: Given a question, brainstorm a question to ask
Input.Category: Ask a question that can’t be answered with just the document.
Input.Description: A good question is related to the document, but the answer isn't found in the document.
Input.Positive_Example_1: What other books were written by the novelist author?
Input.Positive_Example_2: Besides the theory discussed in this document, what other scientific theories explain the given phenomena?

Title: Come up with a question for a document

Input.Category: Ask a question about a table in the document.

Title: Come up with a question for a document
Description: Given a question, brainstorm a question to ask
Input.Category: Ask a question about the structure of the document.

Title: Come up with a question for a document

Input.Category: Ask a question that needs multiple parts of the document to answer.
Input.Description: A good question references sections or pages across different pages or different page numbers.

Title: Come up with a question for a document
Description: Given a question, brainstorm a question to ask
Input.Category: Ask for a summary of parts of the document or the full document.

Input.Positive_Example_1: Can you provide a concise summary of section 2?
